race.description: Level One Wine Bar & Cellars Mdn Hcp
race.comment: COLOMBIANO (11) returned last time with a solid third at this track over 900m. Strips fitter second-up over the longer trip and gets a great chance to get off the mark. FORTE CHEVAL (1) dropped away last start but his two runs prior were full of merit. Will appreciate the longer journey this time. Can bounce back sharply with McDougall reuniting. SOUK (3) has been in the money eight times but couldn't add to the tally when fresh from a spell last start. Led into the straight on that occasion but tired to finish fifth at Canberra. Better with that run under his belt and is expected to prove a handful in front. RAIN QUEEN (9) showed good improvement last start when just falling shy of the placings. Has upside but will just need some luck from the draw. Watch for her charging late.
